<title>USA: Chicago mayor suggests new TIF zone - papers.</title>
<headline>Chicago mayor suggests new TIF zone - papers.</headline>
<dateline>CHICAGO 1997-05-23</dateline>
<text>
<p>Chicago Mayor Richard Daley plans to create a new a tax-increment financing zone for an historic neighborhood inadvertently excluded when the city expanded a TIF zone in and near downtown earlier this year, Chicago newspapers reported Friday.</p>
<p>Chicago expanded its North Loop zone from 15 acres to 139 acres earlier this year to generate $300 million for the city central, but did not include the historic black neighborhood of Bronzeville south of downtown at that time, the Tribune and Sun-Times said.</p>
<p>((--David Bailey, 312-408-8647))</p>
